texts.text: >At the Liberators' Tokyo Branch...
>The air hangs heavy in the living room...
Megakin, Shiang Sun. Will you two cool it.
Yo, that ain't happenin'.
It's been two weeks. We gotta do somethin' about this ASAP...
Yeah, I know. We've been doing what we can these two weeks.
But there's no end in sight at this point.
We've been walking through a tunnel with no light at the end.
Long battles take their toll mentally too, you know?
The ones that can't handle that end up dead on the battlefield.
Your decision-making, reflexes and endurance all slowly degrade.
...Yeah, you're right. Thanks for the reality check.
We'd be puttin' the horse before the cart if we can't act when it matters.
We ain't gonna be able to brush it off by sayin', "Take it easy..."
Yo, we need to relax a bit.
I agree. Seiran and the others are out patrolling too...
But still. Two weeks...
Since it started snowing like crazy out of season in Tokyo...
Yeah. It started with Akihabara. Then everywhere else around it.
It's cold as hell and the whole city's grindin' to a halt.
People are anxious and panic buying, but startin' shit with each other now too.
The police are giving more and more orders, but we only keep hearing gloomy news.
All this snow is causing more accidents and tying up all the ambulances.
No one knows if the stuff being said online is true or fake.
Morals are just a big pile of crap too.
I mean, they fall apart fast in the face of something like this.
We've been seeing a ton of stray demons these past two weeks too.
Something's up, but we don't know what that something is...
We might need to switch to long-term tactics soon.
Something... But nothing like this has ever happened.
...Maybe this has to do with Vanitas and the end...?
>The air still hangs heavy in the living room...
>Then...
This is Seiran! Is anyone back at the hideout?
!! Yo, it's Megakin. What's up?
I sensed something strange while out patrolling and we took a look.
Then we found a demon sitting on top of a spiritual site.
We tried to deal with it, but it called for backup and...
What happened...?
We can't beat them. Nothing we did worked...!
Can't beat them?! What do you mean?!
Give us a sitrep.
We retreated and managed to get away from there.
It seems like they won't stray too far from that spot.
I took a video too. Let me send it over so you can see.
Got it...! I'll play it on my PC.
>The video shows you and Ririn in a battle.
*Chuckle*
*Groan*
Now, you two! One more time!
Yah!!
Hah...!
>You and Ririn order you demons to attack.
>The demons vanish.
*Moan*
>The demons seemed to be in their death throes but...
*Groan*
*Hiss*
>The demons regain their strength...!
It's not working. What the hell are these things?!
They're not even that strong but keep coming back to life!
No good... We need to retreat!
*Shriek*
>A different demon sits quietly behind the demons giving chase.
>The video ends with the camera shaking as everyone runs...
How was it?
About that... What were those things?
They can't be beaten.
And can you get anything on that last demons we saw?
It looked like a skull with a mushroom growing out of it.
That's the one that was sitting there.
And there was a 7 or 8-m radius of unnatural darkness around it.
That demon must have been the one producing it...
But the demons from earlier appeared when we tried to go in.
And nothing worked on the mushroom demon either.
We thought we won, but it just came back to like.
It didn't attack when you were outside of its circle,
but we can't beat it and it's made that spot its home.
We're still close to there... What should we do?
Yo, I don't want to leave it, but we're stuck without a plan.
Make sure it's stayin' there and come back to us.
Copy.
Progress, or rather a setback.
Hopefully we can connect these dots together...
We just gotta find a way yo.
>Somewhere in the city...
>A shady group of people are gathered around a summoning circle, praying...
*Sob*
*Weep*
Baldur, the God of Light imprisoned in hell... Hear us... Answer our prayers...!
Come and grace our world with your light...!!
>The man says his prayer even louder and the circle begins to flash!
Where is this...?
W-what...!! Are you...?!
Leader! It worked... It finally worked!
Are you Baldur, the God of Light?
Indeed. I am Baldur. Are you the one that summoned me...?
Y-yes...!
We did it!! We finally did it!
>The worshippers embrace one another as they shed tears of joy...
This world's going to be saved!
Our prayers reached you! Baldur is finally here with us!
Hmm...
Baldur.
This world is on the brink of destruction.
Snow has been falling for two weeks despite it not being winter.
This must be the Fimbulwinter.
Your death, Baldur, God of Light, would mean the world loses its light,
and usher forth the end of the world, "Ragnarok".
We saw this Fimbulwinter to mean that according to the prophecy you, Baldur,
had lost your life and joined the fallen.
I see. It is as my father was told then... The prophecy...
This world is being shrouded in darkness.
Spiritual sites on the Dragon Stream have begun emitting an evil energy,
and manifesting physically as strange weather phenomena.
We humans are powerless in the face of such forces...
Which is why we then attempted to summon you, Baldur...
You heard our prayers and were brought back to life!
Now that we have Baldur the God of Light here,
light will return to this world and hope for humanity along with it!
We wish you to vanquish this darkness using your powers, oh radiant one.
Your words are kind, but...
Baldur. Please save us, this world...
You are the one that can overturn our fated destruction
>The worshippers gaze upon Baldur with beckoning eyes...
Very well...
You have made your love for this world clear.
Show me where this evil is spreading.
Y-yes!
Everyone, follow Baldur! We must witness his brilliance!
There are those that do not yet know that light and hope have returned.
We must enlighten them!
